decks.notes: This deck focuses on controlling the game through counterspells, removal, and card advantage. It utilizes early interaction such as Fatal Push and Force of Will to disrupt the opponent's game plan, while also generating card advantage with cards like Ancestral Recall and Dig Through Time. The deck aims to outvalue the opponent by efficiently dealing with threats and eventually overpowering them with a combination of card advantage and powerful threats like Lurrus of the Dream-Den. Additionally, the deck has a strong mana base with fetch lands and powerful mana rocks to ensure smooth gameplay.

This deck focuses on using Paradoxical Outcome to combo off and generate a ton of mana and card advantage. It includes cards like Tolarian Academy, Moxen, and artifact mana to ramp up quickly. The deck also includes control elements like Force of Will and removal spells, as well as tutors like Demonic Tutor and Vampiric Tutor to find combo pieces. The goal is to quickly assemble a winning board state that can generate infinite mana or card draw to overpower the opponent and win the game.
